# Red-team a research write-up

Another agent produced a research write-up in this directory. Red-team it against the
writing instructions below: assume it has flaws and find as many concrete, specific
problems as you can. You are not here to praise it or to rewrite it — only to surface
checkable problems.

What's in your CWD (/workspace):
- ./final_writeup.md — the write-up.
- ./final_plots/*.png — the figures. Open each one with your Read tool and look at it; do
  not judge a figure from its caption alone.

The original run is mounted READ-ONLY at /source (with RUN_DIR_STRUCTURE.md and
TRACE_INDEX.md in your CWD), so you can check claims and numbers against the real
artifacts where it matters.

{% include "_writing_instructions.md.j2" %}

Write your findings to ./{{ review_file }} (overwrite it if it exists) as a concrete,
numbered list. For each problem give its location (section, sentence, figure, or appendix
line), what's wrong, and a concrete fix. Order by severity. Do NOT edit ./final_writeup.md
or any figure yourself — only write ./{{ review_file }}.
